decisions-for.stdout_kinds:
Human to stdout. Governed: aligned rows `<id>  <status>  <title>` then an indented continuation `<pad>↳ applies to: <entry>`, then blank line, then e.g. `1 decision(s) govern 'rac/prompts'.` — real: `RAC-KTQ63DR3G4YG  Accepted  ADR-018: RAC Directory as the Canonical Knowledge Root` / `                            ↳ applies to: rac/`. Multi-row example (src/asdecided/mcp/server.py) yields two rows sorted by (id.casefold(), path). Empty in-repo: `No decisions declare scope over 'zzz/nowhere.txt'.`. Outside repo: `'/etc/passwd' is outside the repository — no governing decisions.`. --json to stdout: `{
  "schema_version": "1",
  "query": "rac/prompts",
  "in_repository": true,
  "decisions": [ {id,title,status,path,matching_entry} ]
}` (indent=2). Usage errors to stderr: `rac: not a directory: /nonexistent_dir` and argparse `rac decisions-for: error: the following arguments are required: path`.
